tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The main abnormal findings are elevated creatinine, chloride, and triglycerides, suggesting impaired renal function and dyslipidemia. Other parameters, including glucose, liver enzymes, and electrolytes, are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and cardiovascular risk assessment. Clinical correlation is advised.
